Title: Suzuki V-Strom 650
text: Selling my practically brand new 2018 V-Strom 650, with Super low Miles 3323, (just past break-in) and one of the best extended warranties that's fully transferable! This bike has been meticulously maintained and is the best one you'll find for sale. I've put nearly 17 grand into it in parts and labor. Unfortunately, I just can't ride anymore so my loss is your gain. I've babied this bike and no expense has been spared on it. Below is a list of all the aftermarket parts, which are the best you can find for these bikes. If you have any questions please let me know. Test rides will only happen with cash in hand and a valid MC license. I also have some gear that I may throw in depending on the offer. I also have a ton of extra parts that go with it. This is the most comfortable and versatile bike I've owned that didn't cost 30k. I've had two of these and they are bulletproof I put over 100,000 miles on the last one without any major issues. It has plenty of power for cruising on the highway and is much sportier than it looks. Easily ride two-up, without a care. and it's comfortable on long-distance trips. I averaged around 60mpg on the highway and was much better in town. I'm sure there's something I'm missing but come and take a look and you'll agree it's a great bike. Title: 1968 Honda SCRAMBLER 90
text: Very Rare CL-90 Scrambler in Candy Red. Second year for HONDA's first Off-Road(vs. trail bikes) capable 90cc Motorcycle, based on the famous SUPER 90 street bike, with the 8hp engine! This bike, like it's street cousin, can do an honest 65mph in 4th gear! Still has the original 8hp Carburetor with it's correct intake manifold and air-cleaner boot. Sadly, it's missing the original engine and exhaust, as well as the air-cleaner and seat. Tank also needs new badges and knee-pads. Fortunately, all of these missing parts(including engine) are commonly available new or used on ebay, and all are still made to this day, for sale in the Asian markets(search for Super 90 and CM-200 parts)! Everything there is all original, right down to the tires and grips. The chromed fenders are both straight, but starting to get tarnished. It has the rear passenger foot-pegs too. In storage for almost 20 years. I was going to restore it(they sell for over $2,400), but I'll never have time to finish it. Good rolling project bike. I'll help you load. Asking $1,200 or best offer. Trade considered, but only if you include pictures.

Title: Suzuki V-Strom 650
text: Selling my practically brand new 2018 V-Strom 650, with Super low Miles 3323, (just past break-in) and one of the best extended warranties that's fully transferable! This bike has been meticulously maintained and is the best one you'll find for sale. I've put nearly 17 grand into it in parts and labor. Unfortunately, I just can't ride anymore so my loss is your gain. I've babied this bike and no expense has been spared on it. Below is a list of all the aftermarket parts, which are the best you can find for these bikes. If you have any questions please let me know. Test rides will only happen with cash in hand and a valid MC license. I also have some gear that I may throw in depending on the offer. I also have a ton of extra parts that go with it. This is the most comfortable and versatile bike I've owned that didn't cost 30k. I've had two of these and they are bulletproof I put over 100,000 miles on the last one without any major issues. It has plenty of power for cruising on the highway and is much sportier than it looks. Easily ride two-up, without a care. and it's comfortable on long-distance trips. I averaged around 60mpg on the highway and was much better in town. I'm sure there's something I'm missing but come and take a look and you'll agree it's a great bike. Title: Rare Honda VTX 1300R
text: You don't see many of these bikes and they are real gems. Why? Because they last forever and are light on maintenance. In fact, I have ridden this bike for 9 years and spent around $500, mostly on oil changes. I bought it in 2013 when it was 4 years old from a lady in Tuscon who just contracted ALS. I am retired and ride purely for pleasure - bike still has low mileage and I've kept her nearly in new condition. I really want to sell this bike but please don't lowball me -- I'm a stubborn fellow and I know the market.

Title: KONA STINKY DEE-LUXE
text: Serious downhill Mullet 69er. This is an older and rare build which I intended to complete as an e-bike with a mid-mount Bafang kit but think it is going to be too much for me to handle (I just turned 70 and will go for something a little more sensible). So for 12 to 15 hundred bucks more you could have really fast and stable e-ride at reasonable cost; or leave as is for a unique,tough downhill ride. Approx 19 inch frame with 33inch standover height and amazing 15inch clearance which gives plenty of clearance for a motor. Plenty of triangle space for a battery.DNM double crown inverted fork (which was over $500 alone) and has 20mm thru axle. 29 x 2.6 inch front Easton tubeless wheel (over $300) with new Kenda Hellkat Pro tire. Rear wheel is Mavic D521 q/r with new Kenda Nevegal pro tubed tire. 1x9 setup with oval 36T narrow/wide chainring and Shimano XTR  with new Sunrace 11/32 casette,new Shimano ebike chain. Fox Vanilla R shock. New KS mechanical dropper post. New Answer 810mm flat bar with ergo grips. Beefy Truativ stem and gripshift shifter. Hayes hydraulic brakes with 205mm front and 160 rear discs. Have other bars/shifters/saddles as options Definitely built for the taller rider. Cash only.

Title: Surly Steamroller - 53cm
text: Up for sale is a fixed gear Surly Steamroller.  It has a flip/flop hub, but only the fixed side is set up. It would be super easy to convert to a singlespeed (slap a freewheel on the other side of the hub, flip the wheel around, and coast to your heart's content).   I put brand new Panaracer GravelKing tires on the bike in the fall, still have tons of life left. At 38mm wide, they're provide a smooth ride on all of the gravel bike paths we have around town!  This bike looks beautiful (it's gotten compliments from total strangers multiple times), and is a blast to ride. Unfortunately it's a little too small for me, which discourages me from taking it on longer rides. So it's time to find it a new home! Make me an offer!
